==English==

===Etymology===
The word "ostracism" comes from the Greek word ostrakon (ὄστρακον) meaning "pottery fragment" or "potshard."

===Verb===
'''to ostracize'''
#To exclude someone from society or from a community, by not communicating with or even noticing them, similar to [[shunning]].

